cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.GT, cs.SY, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on D2D communication underlaying cellular networks, which falls under the scope of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The joint channel and power allocation problem can be viewed as an information theory problem, as it involves optimizing the use of limited resources to maximize the efficiency of communication. 
3. cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) - The proposed iterative combinatorial auction algorithm involves game-theoretic concepts, which can be categorized under computer science and game theory. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The problem of resource allocation can also be viewed as a control problem, where the goal is to optimize the performance of a system subject to constraints. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The numerical simulations presented in the paper involve measuring the performance of D2D communication in terms of user throughput, which can be considered a multimedia application.
